\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3.5}{\ignorespaces Full model comparison on 16-day validation set (28,512 rows). RMSLE is the primary optimization metric; MAE and RMSE are on the original sales scale (unit count); R$^2$ measures variance explained. The HGB (raw target) configuration achieves the best MAE, RMSE, and R$^2$ individually at the cost of degraded RMSLE.}}{47}{table.caption.49}\protected@file@percent }
